To subtract, combine like denominators:

\[
-\frac{19}{28}-\frac{7}{28}
=\frac{-19-7}{28}
=\frac{-26}{28}
=-\frac{26}{28}
=-\frac{13}{14}.
\]

Combine the fractions (same denominator 32):

\[
-\,\frac{27}{32} \;-\;\frac{1}{32}
=\frac{-27-1}{32}
=\frac{-28}{32}
=-\frac{7}{8}.
\]

Combine the like terms over the common denominator a:

\[
- \frac{17}{a} \;-\;\frac{5}{a}
=\frac{-17 - 5}{a}
=\frac{-22}{a}
=-\frac{22}{a}.
\]

To combine, note all terms have denominator 9 and are negative:

\[
-\frac{2}{9} + \bigl(-\frac{4}{9}\bigr) - \frac{7}{9}
= -\frac{2+4+7}{9}
= -\frac{13}{9}.
\]

To evaluate \(-\tfrac{3}{8}-y\) at \(y=-\tfrac{5}{2}\), substitute and simplify:

\[
-\frac{3}{8}-\bigl(-\tfrac{5}{2}\bigr)
\;=\;
-\frac{3}{8} + \frac{5}{2}
\;=\;
-\frac{3}{8} + \frac{20}{8}
\;=\;
\frac{17}{8}.
\]
